cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.SOC, cs.MM

This paper belongs to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society) because it analyzes the transparency of online political advertising on social media platforms. It also involves the use of data analysis and machine learning techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses limitations and weaknesses in the current implementation of transparency archives, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper touches on the topic of deceptive online communities, which could relate to the sub-category of cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences).
